article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast 60, Bethune-Cookman 57
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Kyle Matheney's only points of the game -- three free throws in the final 33.8 seconds -- sealed Florida Gulf Coast's 60-57 win over Bethune Cookman on Monday night. Casey Wohlleb's 15 points led Florida Gulf Coast in the school's Division I debut. Landon Adler added 12 points and Adam Liddell scored 10. John Holmes led Bethune-Cookman (0-2) with 19 points and Dewayne Pettus scored 12. Matheney's free throws stopped a comeback by the Wildcats, which trailed by 14 points with 8:34 to play. Bethune-Cookman went on an 18-3 run and took the lead by one point, 52-51, on a Holmes free throw with 2:41 left. Liddell responded with an inside basket and two quick free throws to put the Eagles back up, 55-52, with 1:44 in the game. Bethune-Cookman closed it to one point two more times, but Matheney's free throws sealed it for the Eagles.
